						<summary>

						<p>Three stray stones lying in the precincts of the Lōkanāthēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 9th century.</p>						

						<p>The first two fragments seem to refer to a gift. The third, in Tamil, to the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍalika</hi> of Pudu-nāḍu.</p>						

